03:00.639 --> 03:03.336
The pain they caused Beth.

03:04.863 --> 03:07.922
Beth. Amberleigh's mother?

03:07.922 --> 03:11.211
Mr. Nate Royce helped me
understand the pain she went through.

03:11.211 --> 03:14.139
Nate Royce. That's their
next door neighbor.

03:14.139 --> 03:15.721
Beth's protector,

03:15.721 --> 03:19.764
and my email confidant
for the last three months.

03:25.974 --> 03:28.689
He turned me in, didn't he?

03:30.613 --> 03:32.078
The DA didn't brief us.

03:32.078 --> 03:35.266
We found out about this thing
an hour before we got on the plane.

03:35.266 --> 03:37.304
The time had come.

03:37.304 --> 03:40.215
Sorry, time? To confess?

03:40.215 --> 03:46.060
The time the world heard
the story of a pure love,

03:46.060 --> 03:51.529
and of a world so corrupt,
it had to force that love into darkness...

03:53.472 --> 03:56.127
where it perished.

04:12.562 --> 04:15.295
They all look sweet
when they're sleeping.

04:15.295 --> 04:18.829
But this is one sick puppy.

04:18.829 --> 04:21.298
He is Simon Henry Fife,

04:21.298 --> 04:24.224
and tonight he is in NYPD custody.

04:24.224 --> 04:26.731
After 14 years,

04:26.731 --> 04:30.065
the Halloween murder
of Amberleigh Harner...

04:30.065 --> 04:33.769
this angel, killed in the basement
of her Brooklyn home,

04:33.769 --> 04:36.365
has at last been solved.

04:36.365 --> 04:39.619
Bethany Harner, Amberleigh's mother,

04:39.619 --> 04:41.830
are there any words?

04:41.830 --> 04:47.168
I have waited so long
for justice, Faith.

04:47.168 --> 04:49.495
She was...

04:49.495 --> 04:50.988
my star.

04:50.988 --> 04:55.287
Your neighbor, Mr. Nate Royce,
led them to the killer.

04:55.287 --> 04:58.774
Without your perseverance,
Fife would still be in Vietnam.

04:58.774 --> 05:00.395
If you haven't lost your lunch yet,

05:00.395 --> 05:02.488
here's another photo.

05:02.801 --> 05:05.807
Nate, how did you trap this predator?

05:05.807 --> 05:08.605
He emailed me about three months ago.

05:08.605 --> 05:10.022
Because of your book?

05:10.022 --> 05:12.033
He wasn't the first sicko to reach out,

05:12.033 --> 05:15.428
but something in his emails unsettled me.

05:17.042 --> 05:19.200
I wonder what it was.

05:19.200 --> 05:23.087
I stopped reading when I got to Fife's line
about how he made love to Amberleigh

05:23.087 --> 05:25.067
while commingling their blood.

05:25.067 --> 05:28.415
There was no blood in the basement,
except for Amberleigh's.

05:33.955 --> 05:36.328
How much champagne
did you let him drink?

05:36.328 --> 05:38.534
Hope you got something good out of him.

05:38.534 --> 05:41.596
Well, he idealizes children,
he demonizes adults.

05:41.596 --> 05:45.494
He was most likely abused by a parent.

05:45.494 --> 05:49.173
I don't suppose you asked him if he was
in Brooklyn on Halloween night, 1992?

05:49.173 --> 05:51.623
Well, that's not exactly
a first interview question.

05:51.623 --> 05:55.561
Detective, I don't care about Fife's
childhood pain or his world view.

05:55.561 --> 05:57.384
Brooklyn homicide botched this case.
That's why it was kicked to us.

05:57.384 --> 05:59.789
- I was just trying to gain his trust.
- That's why it was kicked to us.

05:59.789 --> 06:01.252
Before Fife lawyers up...

06:01.252 --> 06:02.550
What do you want me to do,
go old school,

06:02.550 --> 06:05.672
slap him around with a phone book
until he confesses?

06:07.308 --> 06:09.030
I want the same thing you want,

06:09.030 --> 06:12.329
to be absolutely sure
he killed Amberleigh.

06:15.692 --> 06:17.084
Oh, he killed her.

06:17.084 --> 06:19.486
The detail in his emails,
his knowledge of her home...

06:19.486 --> 06:21.744
Amberleigh's become an icon
since her death.

06:21.744 --> 06:23.407
There's a lot of information out there.

06:23.407 --> 06:24.556
Yes, I know, detectives.

06:24.556 --> 06:27.174
And hundreds of people confessed to
killing the Lindbergh baby,

06:27.174 --> 06:29.285
- but Hauptmann did it.
- Okay, fine.

06:29.285 --> 06:31.528
Is there anything linking Fife
to the scene of the crime?

06:31.528 --> 06:33.733
NYPD never secured the crime scene.

06:33.733 --> 06:35.609
A dozen people tramped through
that basement

06:35.609 --> 06:37.014
before her body was found.

06:37.014 --> 06:38.726
So that's a no?

06:39.125 --> 06:41.667
There was a ransom call
from a phone booth at night.

06:41.667 --> 06:42.583
A woman's voice, right?

06:42.583 --> 06:44.224
"Feminine," I believe, is the word.

06:44.224 --> 06:46.897
And Fife? Well, you've met him.

06:46.897 --> 06:50.371
Any proof Fife ever met Amberleigh,
stalked her?

06:50.371 --> 06:51.963
Our investigators are looking into it.

06:51.963 --> 06:53.483
In the meantime, let's arraign him.

06:53.483 --> 06:55.193
In the meantime, let's not.

06:55.193 --> 06:57.318
He's comfortable in our custody.

06:57.318 --> 06:59.262
The longer we hold him,
the more he talks,

06:59.262 --> 07:01.735
the better you look when you convict.

07:02.548 --> 07:04.809
- I'd have to talk to...
- Go ahead.

07:04.809 --> 07:06.432
We'll wait.

07:11.005 --> 07:12.838
24 hours, if we're lucky.

07:12.838 --> 07:15.960
A 14-year-old unsolved case,
24 hours to solve it?

07:15.960 --> 07:18.092
Maybe someone close
to Amberleigh can place him.

07:18.092 --> 07:22.305
It won't be easy,
the mother hasn't spoken to NYPD
since the night of the murder.

07:22.305 --> 07:23.526
And the ex-husband?

07:23.526 --> 07:25.137
Away on business the night of the murder,

07:25.137 --> 07:26.984
remarried, and moved out west.

07:26.984 --> 07:28.953
Pay a visit to Amberleigh's mother.

07:28.953 --> 07:30.688
Find out if she had ever seen Fife

07:30.688 --> 07:33.572
before he crawled out
of his Vietnamese sewer.

07:42.320 --> 07:44.593
She's away, detectives.

07:46.564 --> 07:49.395
You're Nate Royce, the author?

07:49.395 --> 07:52.342
The friend and neighbor.

07:52.666 --> 07:56.267
Beth disappears around Halloween,
too many gawkers coming by the house.

07:56.267 --> 07:58.611
I'm surprised she kept this home.

07:58.611 --> 08:00.960
It's been hard for her to move on.

08:00.960 --> 08:03.388
I think now she'll be able to.

08:03.718 --> 08:06.113
You mean, if Fife is guilty.

08:06.780 --> 08:09.261
Did you ever see Fife
watching Amberleigh?

08:09.261 --> 08:14.506
No, but he knew about the blood
on the couch, the open dryer door.

08:14.506 --> 08:17.448
Yeah, but still, you know, her murder,

08:17.448 --> 08:20.635
this home invasion homicide,
it was bold.

08:20.900 --> 08:25.820
And, uh, you've been fooled
by his whimsical child/man character.

08:25.820 --> 08:27.643
You think it's an act, a persona?

08:27.643 --> 08:30.530
That he might have created this...

08:30.530 --> 08:32.549
love affair he has with Amberleigh?

08:32.549 --> 08:34.976
I think he's pathological,
not creative.

08:34.976 --> 08:36.672
Well, you'd know.

08:36.672 --> 08:37.912
He creates characters.

08:37.912 --> 08:39.357
You were a novelist, weren't you?

08:39.357 --> 08:42.803
I was, until that awful night.

08:42.803 --> 08:47.028
You found a way to be of service.
Your book, website.

08:47.028 --> 08:50.070
I did what I could for Amberleigh.

08:50.333 --> 08:52.027
It's been...

08:52.027 --> 08:53.556
it's been hell.

08:53.556 --> 08:55.836
My wife died four years
after Amberleigh,

08:55.836 --> 08:59.513
and I've had to raise
our young son alone.

08:59.513 --> 09:02.690
Well, Beth Harner
is very lucky to have you.

09:02.690 --> 09:04.397
And we need to get in touch with her.

09:04.397 --> 09:07.217
She won't talk to NYPD,
you know that.

09:07.217 --> 09:09.231
Mr. Royce, we know that
mistakes were made.

09:09.231 --> 09:11.632
I could try to talk to her.

09:11.632 --> 09:14.512
She'll be angry if she knows
I even let you walk on her property.

09:14.512 --> 09:16.736
It's the captain.
Fife is getting antsy.

09:16.736 --> 09:18.797
He wants to speak to you.

09:21.456 --> 09:23.388
Where's Bobby?
He believes me.

09:23.388 --> 09:24.754
He does, I don't.

09:24.754 --> 09:26.598
You ask me,
you made the whole thing up.

09:26.598 --> 09:29.274
- That's crazy.
- You said it.

09:30.509 --> 09:32.574
She was my girlfriend.

09:32.574 --> 09:35.333
Right. And you met her where?

09:35.577 --> 09:37.127
We met at her school.

09:37.127 --> 09:38.979
I worked as a nurse.

09:38.979 --> 09:41.637
And on Halloween night...

09:41.847 --> 09:43.965
I made love to her.

09:43.965 --> 09:47.882
There were no signs of love-making.

09:47.882 --> 09:49.760
You don't believe me.
You want proof?

09:49.760 --> 09:51.336
How about her stomach contents?

09:51.336 --> 09:52.717
Halloween?

09:52.717 --> 09:54.184
You're gonna guess candy.

09:54.184 --> 09:56.550
Just sesame logs.

09:56.883 --> 09:58.865
She loved them.

10:00.242 --> 10:02.785
I'm checking, checking.

10:03.515 --> 10:05.099
They blacked it out.

10:05.099 --> 10:09.063
She gorged on sweet honey
sesame candy

10:09.063 --> 10:11.253
while I made love to her...

10:11.253 --> 10:13.468
on the night...

10:13.727 --> 10:15.722
she left us.

10:26.678 --> 10:28.078
The ME confirmed it.

10:28.078 --> 10:30.972
Amberleigh ate sesame candy
in the last hours of her life.

10:30.972 --> 10:33.450
That was kept out of the autopsy report.

10:33.450 --> 10:36.102
Never published, never leaked.

10:36.102 --> 10:37.391
The department of Ed confirms

10:37.391 --> 10:41.865
Fife worked as a nurse at Amberleigh's
school for two weeks that September.

10:41.865 --> 10:44.207
A lot of people worked at her school.

10:44.207 --> 10:46.084
I told the DA we'd strengthen her case.

10:46.084 --> 10:46.949
You've done that.

10:46.949 --> 10:50.248
The DA told you that we had 24 hours.

10:50.248 --> 10:52.103
We haven't been into the crime scene.

10:52.103 --> 10:53.512
We haven't interviewed Beth.

10:53.512 --> 10:54.975
You know the DA's office.

10:54.975 --> 10:56.368
This case collapses,

10:56.368 --> 10:59.245
they'll spin it so everybody thinks
we botched it again.

10:59.245 --> 11:00.825
And this case collapses how?

11:00.825 --> 11:02.384
The ransom demand.

11:02.384 --> 11:05.024
The caller said,
"we have your whore daughter."

11:05.024 --> 11:08.460
Fife thinks he made
gentle love to Amberleigh.

11:08.460 --> 11:10.554
Different fantasy.

11:10.554 --> 11:12.536
Okay. Keep the clock running.

11:12.536 --> 11:14.538
Get a search warrant
for the Harner home.

11:14.538 --> 11:17.106
Track down the detective who
first responded to the scene.

11:17.106 --> 11:18.626
It wasn't a detective.

11:18.626 --> 11:21.506
She was a rookie, Linda Bonnardi.

11:22.584 --> 11:24.905
Right, I forgot.
She'd just graduated.

11:24.905 --> 11:26.036
Four months out.

11:26.036 --> 11:27.814
A year later, when I went to the academy,

11:27.814 --> 11:31.067
they were using her
as an example in class,

11:31.067 --> 11:33.877
to prove that women
were too emotional to be cops.

11:33.877 --> 11:36.629
She left the force in disgrace.

11:37.346 --> 11:38.749
Find her.

11:52.009 --> 11:53.897
Happy Halloween.

11:55.577 --> 11:59.673
4 A.M. the mother, Beth,
she's totally hysterical.

11:59.673 --> 12:03.420
Said she heard the kid scream,
ran to her bedroom.

12:03.420 --> 12:05.309
Kid's gone.

12:07.085 --> 12:10.364
10 or 15 minutes later,
she gets a ransom call.

12:10.364 --> 12:12.191
"We have your whore daughter."

12:12.191 --> 12:14.876
"We'll call back at 6.
Don't tell anyone."

12:14.876 --> 12:16.411
That's when she called us.

12:16.411 --> 12:19.655
And you searched the house?

12:19.655 --> 12:22.368
And Matt interviewed Beth.

12:22.368 --> 12:23.615
Big mistake.

12:23.615 --> 12:26.077
Beth had made phone calls
before we arrived.

12:26.077 --> 12:29.049
So while I'm searching,
people keep showing up.

12:29.049 --> 12:30.587
People? The Royces.

12:30.587 --> 12:32.713
You mean Nate and Madeline?

12:32.713 --> 12:34.490
And their kid.

12:34.490 --> 12:35.878
Weird, right?

12:35.878 --> 12:38.161
And you didn't call for backup?

12:38.161 --> 12:39.713
I thought it was a prank.

12:39.713 --> 12:41.806
But there was a ransom call.

12:42.712 --> 12:43.899
I didn't believe her.

12:43.899 --> 12:45.255
You get a call like that,

12:45.255 --> 12:47.249
"we have your whore daughter,
don't tell anybody,"

12:47.249 --> 12:49.717
and you invite ten friends over?

12:49.717 --> 12:51.630
Mm-hmm, I see your point.

12:51.630 --> 12:52.966
And the caller,

12:52.966 --> 12:54.761
she said she'd call back at 6.

12:54.761 --> 12:57.988
At 6, Beth is on the phone.

12:58.202 --> 13:00.139
I tell her, "hang up."

13:00.139 --> 13:04.051
That 6 o'clock call should've been
all she was thinking about.

13:05.996 --> 13:08.622
Who went into the basement?

13:08.622 --> 13:11.172
I did, with Beth.

13:31.787 --> 13:33.991
Nothing's changed.

13:40.710 --> 13:42.682
That cellar door wasn't open,

13:42.682 --> 13:45.734
but it was not in its locked position.

13:45.972 --> 13:47.197
You noticed that?

13:47.197 --> 13:50.296
No. Beth did, uh...
right away.

13:51.130 --> 13:54.284
Then I noticed the dryer door ajar.

13:54.505 --> 13:56.413
The light is on.

13:56.774 --> 13:58.592
I open it.

14:00.367 --> 14:03.321
For a second, I thought
she was sleeping.

14:07.857 --> 14:11.461
You let Beth take the body out.

14:11.670 --> 14:14.420
I let her lead me to the body.

14:15.528 --> 14:17.280
She killed her daughter.

14:17.280 --> 14:19.560
And because of me,

14:19.848 --> 14:21.870
she got away with it.

14:29.158 --> 14:30.335
Thank you.

14:30.543 --> 14:33.254
Don't let her get away
with it this time.

14:35.773 --> 14:38.077
She was a female rookie,
wanted to prove herself,

14:38.077 --> 14:40.915
ended up making it harder
on the rest of us.

14:40.915 --> 14:46.355
Yeah, Beth Harner's behavior was
very, very strange that morning but,

14:46.355 --> 14:52.230
it's another rookie cop's mistake
to think that strange behavior equals guilt.

14:52.731 --> 14:54.464
Nate's still on duty.

14:54.464 --> 14:56.740
Mm-hmm, and he's on the phone.

14:56.740 --> 14:58.638
I wonder who he's talking to.

14:58.979 --> 15:00.906
No. There is nothing else.

15:00.906 --> 15:03.329
The DA has copies of everything.

15:03.329 --> 15:07.529
You're not writing a new book
about the case, are you?

15:07.529 --> 15:09.231
I'm just polishing it now, actually.

15:09.231 --> 15:11.330
Put you back on that bestsellers list.

15:11.330 --> 15:13.425
I am on your side.

15:13.645 --> 15:15.260
Then put us in touch with Beth Harner.

15:15.260 --> 15:17.386
- She would kill me, if I...
- What if I just hit the "redial"?

15:17.386 --> 15:19.535
Put that down! Please.

15:20.979 --> 15:23.889
I'm sorry,
I just try to protect her.

15:23.889 --> 15:25.815
Look, she told me
she had never met Fife.

15:25.815 --> 15:28.372
We like to get our information firsthand.

15:28.372 --> 15:31.501
And you wouldn't want something
to delay the publication of your book,

15:31.501 --> 15:34.851
like, say, a subpoena of your notes?

15:38.143 --> 15:38.977
Dad.

15:38.977 --> 15:40.945
Jamie, I thought you had a meeting.

15:40.945 --> 15:42.679
Hello to you too, dad.

15:42.679 --> 15:44.181
Everything okay?

15:44.181 --> 15:49.556
Yes, I'm just helping these detectives
get in touch with Beth.

15:50.157 --> 15:53.352
I am surprised
you even want my opinion.

15:53.352 --> 15:57.023
The New York police department
never believed a word I said.

15:57.023 --> 15:58.600
And that's the guy.

15:58.600 --> 16:00.975
I never saw him in the schoolyard,
but that's the guy.

16:00.975 --> 16:02.702
You took your daughter to school?

16:02.702 --> 16:05.400
I took my daughter to school every day.

16:06.570 --> 16:09.698
Unless, of course, she was,
please don't touch anything.

16:10.032 --> 16:13.083
Unless, of course, she was working.

16:13.083 --> 16:17.736
And then, we would run lines
together for her auditions.

16:17.736 --> 16:19.950
You'd run lines?

16:20.140 --> 16:21.892
You were an actress too, right?

16:21.892 --> 16:23.906
Oh, no, uh, no.

16:23.906 --> 16:27.841
Amberleigh was truly gifted.

16:27.841 --> 16:29.553
I was, well,

16:29.553 --> 16:32.367
I danced in the chorus
of a couple of shows,

16:32.367 --> 16:34.601
and weak knees ended that dream.

16:34.601 --> 16:36.903
Oh, your knees look fine.

16:36.903 --> 16:41.543
And your talent wasn't wasted.
You gave it to Amberleigh.

16:41.543 --> 16:43.904
Thank you very much.

16:43.904 --> 16:46.936
But it wasn't just me.
I mean, we had Jenna.

16:46.936 --> 16:48.171
Jenna?

16:48.171 --> 16:49.793
Yes.

16:49.793 --> 16:51.950
Amberleigh's acting coach...

16:51.950 --> 16:54.885
for all of her commercials,

16:54.885 --> 16:57.570
even the last one that she did
in September in L.A.

16:57.570 --> 16:59.074
Sep, September?

16:59.074 --> 17:01.351
Yes, right before...

17:06.526 --> 17:10.810
You know, Amberleigh loved acting.

17:12.255 --> 17:14.992
She loved Hollywood.

17:18.715 --> 17:21.792
Sweet and juicy.

17:23.588 --> 17:26.016
Her last commercial, it never aired.

17:26.016 --> 17:28.186
As you can see,
the camera loved her.

17:28.186 --> 17:29.750
Did she love the camera?

17:29.750 --> 17:31.503
That's a lot of pressure
on a young girl.

17:31.503 --> 17:33.012
Amberleigh was a professional.

17:33.012 --> 17:36.573
Even when she was unhappy,
she never projected it on-screen.

17:36.573 --> 17:38.959
Unhappy? Her mother said
that she loved acting.

17:38.959 --> 17:40.690
Oh, she did.

17:40.690 --> 17:42.979
This is the only time
I heard her complain.

17:42.979 --> 17:44.581
The shoot kept getting postponed.

17:44.581 --> 17:47.661
She was nervous about missing
the start of school.

17:48.780 --> 17:51.361
Do you happen to remember the dates?

17:51.361 --> 17:53.415
It's on the box sleeve.

17:53.764 --> 17:56.938
First two weeks, September 1992.

17:56.938 --> 17:58.831
Amberleigh was miserable.

17:58.831 --> 18:01.693
But you never saw it on her face.

18:08.383 --> 18:11.058
Sweet and juicy.

18:13.912 --> 18:16.455
Sweet and juicy.

18:25.606 --> 18:28.248
I jimmied the lock on the cellar door.

18:28.248 --> 18:30.315
That's how I got in.

18:30.604 --> 18:33.573
Simon, that door wasn't jimmied.

18:33.573 --> 18:34.826
The door was unlocked.

18:34.826 --> 18:36.195
No.

18:37.067 --> 18:39.223
That can't be.

18:40.853 --> 18:43.267
I snuck in through the cellar door.

18:43.267 --> 18:45.968
We'll put that aside for a moment.

18:46.825 --> 18:50.076
What do you do, usually, on Halloween?

18:50.076 --> 18:52.796
I stay home, hand out candy.

18:53.248 --> 18:55.166
And it must be your favorite
night of the year,

18:55.166 --> 18:59.848
these little girls, dressed in costume.

18:59.848 --> 19:03.432
Princesses, fairies...

19:03.432 --> 19:06.143
with sparkling wings,
ribbons in their hair...

19:06.143 --> 19:08.739
Your favorite night of the year.

19:11.267 --> 19:13.638
Why did you go out?

19:18.371 --> 19:20.147
I mean, you must have went out.

19:20.147 --> 19:23.113
You said that you were
with Amberleigh that night.

19:23.113 --> 19:25.479
That's right. / Do you remember
what she was dressed as?

19:25.479 --> 19:27.456
She was a little Genie.

19:27.456 --> 19:32.203
You remember everything
about Amberleigh, don't you?

19:33.567 --> 19:37.016
First day of school,
she wore a yellow dress,

19:37.016 --> 19:41.379
and little white ankle socks
with white shoes.

19:41.772 --> 19:43.580
You can see that, can't you?

19:43.580 --> 19:46.517
I mean, you can see it in your mind's eye,
the little yellow dress?

19:46.517 --> 19:49.451
Skipping at recess.

19:49.738 --> 19:51.855
So beautiful.

19:54.295 --> 19:59.124
Simon, you and Amberleigh
were never in that school together.

19:59.958 --> 20:03.186
Amberleigh was in Los Angeles
for the first two weeks of school,

20:03.186 --> 20:06.695
and you were fired
before she came back.

20:06.695 --> 20:08.857
She was in Los Angeles?

20:08.880 --> 20:11.857
- Then what about the sesame candy?
- I don't know.

20:11.857 --> 20:14.894
Maybe somebody told you.
Maybe you read it.

20:17.481 --> 20:22.190
It must have been Beth,
in one of her emails.

20:26.573 --> 20:29.504
Amberleigh's mother sent you an email?

20:30.579 --> 20:33.682
She made me promise not to tell anyone.

20:35.700 --> 20:40.136
No one knows, not Nate Royce,
not the DA.

20:44.933 --> 20:47.580
You won't tell anyone, will you?

20:56.804 --> 20:58.673
He may not have murdered Amberleigh,

20:58.673 --> 21:02.245
but I wouldn't let him within
a hundred miles of my nieces.

21:02.245 --> 21:03.517
Well, for what it's worth,

21:03.517 --> 21:06.038
Fife has agreed to enter
a monitored program.

21:06.038 --> 21:09.172
And the ADA says
we ruined her investigation,

21:09.172 --> 21:12.009
so now it's on us to solve.

21:12.933 --> 21:17.077
We have to ask Beth Harner
about these emails she sent to Fife.

21:17.077 --> 21:21.033
Not me. He's the one she was
making goo-goo eyes with.

21:21.748 --> 21:22.887
What's your take on her?

21:22.887 --> 21:25.299
Well, she's off, at times,
in her affect.

21:25.299 --> 21:27.718
You know, she smiles
when she's upset.

21:27.718 --> 21:28.880
She craves attention.

21:28.880 --> 21:30.917
You can see why people
made her as a suspect.

21:30.917 --> 21:32.318
A suspect without a motive.

21:32.318 --> 21:34.584
She was living through her daughter.

21:34.584 --> 21:39.459
If Amberleigh ever balked
at Beth's dream for her...

21:39.459 --> 21:42.013
You said she craves attention.
Give her some.

21:42.013 --> 21:44.935
You gained Fife's trust,
gain hers.

