Coming!

22:28.156 --> 22:29.366
Wel...

22:32.171 --> 22:35.086
Oh, I wasn't expecting
the both of yous.

22:35.086 --> 22:37.388
Actually, I was just
dropping my partner off.

22:37.388 --> 22:39.763
Yeah, well, maybe next time.
Come in.

22:39.763 --> 22:42.074
Call me, if you need a ride home.

22:42.873 --> 22:44.165
Bye.

22:47.560 --> 22:51.316
I'm sorry you haven't had closure.

22:53.194 --> 22:56.447
But the case will remain open, right?

22:56.447 --> 22:57.919
Yeah, the case will stay open.

22:57.919 --> 23:00.251
No, I don't mean that. I mean...

23:00.251 --> 23:02.819
you'll be the one who calls me,
who tells me things,

23:02.819 --> 23:05.534
who keeps me updated?

23:06.201 --> 23:08.162
- Okay.
- Okay?

23:16.225 --> 23:20.458
You know, you seem like a man
who is dedicated to his work.

23:20.458 --> 23:22.879
Too much maybe.

23:23.907 --> 23:26.622
Like you were to Amberleigh.

23:31.244 --> 23:32.475
All right, I did it.

23:32.475 --> 23:34.168
I mean, I pushed her.

23:34.168 --> 23:37.545
But Amberleigh wanted to stop acting.

23:37.545 --> 23:40.296
A few months before she died,

23:40.296 --> 23:43.589
she told me that it wasn't
fun for her anymore.

23:43.589 --> 23:45.489
What? The auditions,
watching her weight?

23:45.489 --> 23:46.951
Yes.

23:48.223 --> 23:50.020
Halloween...

23:50.020 --> 23:52.659
how did, how did you
handle the candy?

23:52.659 --> 23:55.487
Amberleigh was allowed
to keep ten pieces

23:55.487 --> 24:00.116
and then she had to give the rest away.

24:00.352 --> 24:01.928
To her friends.

24:05.018 --> 24:09.899
The names of these kids that went
trick-or-treating with her, you remember them?

24:09.899 --> 24:12.387
Of course I remember.

24:16.557 --> 24:18.460
- Brianna.
- Okay.

24:18.460 --> 24:20.947
From down the street.
You know? She, oh,

24:20.947 --> 24:25.892
she worshipped Amberleigh.
She worshipped Amberleigh.

24:26.270 --> 24:29.400
And the Perlman twins.

24:29.400 --> 24:33.899
And Jamie, Nate's son.

24:33.899 --> 24:36.515
Nate Royce's son,
who lived next door?

24:36.515 --> 24:39.771
- He still does.
- Okay.

24:45.450 --> 24:48.091
Detective Goren...

24:49.847 --> 24:53.592
I've never told this to anyone before.

24:55.215 --> 25:00.462
The night that my baby was murdered,

25:01.920 --> 25:06.040
she wanted to eat
an extra piece of candy,

25:06.040 --> 25:09.002
just one more little piece of candy.

25:09.002 --> 25:11.019
And I wouldn't let her have it.

25:11.019 --> 25:13.928
She went to bed, she was crying.
She was angry with me.

25:13.928 --> 25:15.865
I didn't even kiss her good night.

25:15.865 --> 25:18.667
There's a book, okay?

25:18.667 --> 25:20.802
It's about grieving.

25:20.802 --> 25:23.264
And I'm sorry, but I can't
remember the name of it,

25:23.264 --> 25:27.605
but it could, it could help.
I could email it to you.

25:27.605 --> 25:29.426
Thank you.

25:30.527 --> 25:34.298
But I don't have, um, the internet.

25:34.298 --> 25:36.131
You don't have an email account?

25:36.131 --> 25:38.076
No.

25:38.440 --> 25:42.907
If someone wants to send me a sympathy
note or anything like that, you know,

25:42.907 --> 25:47.799
they, um, email it, or send it,
or whatever it's called,

25:47.799 --> 25:52.986
to Nate, and then Nate
brings it to me.

25:53.852 --> 25:55.425
Okay.

25:56.200 --> 25:59.485
Happy Halloween!

25:59.485 --> 26:02.698
Oh, what has you guys get tonight?

26:06.675 --> 26:08.652
Anything good?

26:08.966 --> 26:10.404
Stop, Amberleigh.
Stop tickling me.

26:10.404 --> 26:12.434
Tell us what your costumes are.

26:12.434 --> 26:13.662
I'm a Genie.

26:13.662 --> 26:15.010
And I'm a prince.

26:15.010 --> 26:17.911
Oh, a prince!
Isn't he handsome, Amberleigh?

26:17.911 --> 26:22.025
Isn't Jamie a handsome
prince Charming, huh?

26:22.417 --> 26:23.221
Yeah.

26:23.221 --> 26:25.924
So Beth told me she didn't email Fife

26:25.924 --> 26:27.995
about Amberleigh's stomach contents.

26:27.995 --> 26:31.667
And she didn't know about
Amberleigh's candy binge.

26:31.667 --> 26:34.161
I wonder if prince Jamie did.

26:43.982 --> 26:46.110
I was at Amberleigh's
for the candy swap,

26:46.110 --> 26:48.218
and then my parents took me home.

26:49.435 --> 26:53.269
What kind of candy did Amberleigh
get at the swap?

26:53.269 --> 26:54.996
Sesame logs.

26:54.996 --> 26:58.510
She got, like, 30 of them
'cause nobody else liked them.

26:59.489 --> 27:03.207
Halloween, the anniversary.
It must hard for you.

27:03.207 --> 27:06.230
Well, it's two anniversaries
for me, so, yeah, I guess.

27:06.230 --> 27:10.671
My mom died on Halloween too,
four years after, in a car wreck.

27:10.671 --> 27:12.006
She was drinking,

27:12.006 --> 27:13.683
but she didn't hurt anybody else.

27:13.683 --> 27:16.783
But that must have hurt you a lot.

27:18.236 --> 27:19.981
I'm, I'm okay.

27:19.981 --> 27:22.469
I gotta go.
I got a meeting.

27:22.469 --> 27:24.697
- Faculty?
- Teach?

27:24.697 --> 27:25.630
No.

27:25.630 --> 27:29.313
Uh, I'm still a student,
but this is a meeting, meeting.

27:30.091 --> 27:31.999
- AA?
- NA.

27:31.999 --> 27:34.542
Alcohol led to drugs.

27:35.176 --> 27:37.081
How long have you been sober?

27:37.081 --> 27:38.886
14 weeks.

27:38.886 --> 27:41.238
But I was addicted for 14 years.

27:41.238 --> 27:43.184
What step are you on?

27:43.184 --> 27:44.501
Fifth.

27:44.501 --> 27:46.153
Five...

27:46.363 --> 27:49.390
to admit the exact nature of your wrongs,

27:49.390 --> 27:51.961
to stop lying.

27:54.645 --> 27:57.243
Are you ready to do that?

28:03.653 --> 28:05.174
Yeah.

28:06.584 --> 28:08.533
Yeah, I am.

28:15.949 --> 28:17.434
Halloween night,

28:17.434 --> 28:19.638
Amberleigh looked so pretty,

28:19.638 --> 28:23.890
and she kept trying to tickle me.

28:23.890 --> 28:26.394
I misunderstood.

28:26.701 --> 28:30.015
That night, later, I couldn't sleep.

28:30.015 --> 28:32.146
I snuck into her house.

28:32.146 --> 28:36.246
I said we should go to the basement
and eat all our candy.

28:38.589 --> 28:41.475
Okay. You ate candy. Then?

28:42.507 --> 28:45.932
Um, I tried to kiss her,

28:45.932 --> 28:48.519
and she screamed.

28:48.519 --> 28:50.653
I tried to cover her mouth,

28:50.653 --> 28:53.706
but I hit her nose instead.

28:53.706 --> 28:55.667
She started to bleed.

28:55.667 --> 28:57.976
She was really crying.

28:58.674 --> 29:03.899
I pushed her face into the couch
to keep her quiet.

29:07.058 --> 29:08.648
I was so scared, you know?

29:08.648 --> 29:11.485
I didn't mean to kill her.

29:11.485 --> 29:14.301
Then you put her body in the dryer.

29:14.301 --> 29:16.144
No, I went home.

29:16.144 --> 29:20.630
And there was blood on my shirt.

29:20.630 --> 29:24.271
My mom told me to go to bed,
let her handle it.

29:24.271 --> 29:26.661
And I thought she was gonna
explain it to Beth.

29:26.661 --> 29:28.995
I waited at my window.

29:28.995 --> 29:33.611
Um, mom got in the car and drove off.

29:33.611 --> 29:36.268
She probably went
to make the ransom call.

29:36.268 --> 29:38.914
Why do you think she did that?

29:39.764 --> 29:43.628
I think she meant
to get rid of the body.

29:43.628 --> 29:47.655
She must've panicked
and hid Amberleigh in the dryer.

29:51.357 --> 29:53.825
I know you're gonna tell Beth.

29:55.697 --> 29:59.112
If she'll let me,
I'd like to speak to her.

30:00.519 --> 30:03.267
You care about Beth.

30:03.671 --> 30:09.532
Jamie, why did you email Simon Fife
pretending to be Beth?

30:12.675 --> 30:15.746
I don't remember doing that.

30:18.472 --> 30:22.675
But all those years of drug use,
you know, I have gaps.

30:22.675 --> 30:26.034
Um, they have meetings in jail, right?

30:26.320 --> 30:28.412
They do.

30:32.460 --> 30:34.615
Do you think your dad blames himself

30:34.615 --> 30:36.962
for what happened to you
after Amberleigh's murder?

30:36.962 --> 30:39.433
My dad didn't know about any of this.

30:39.433 --> 30:41.798
He was asleep.
We never told him.

30:41.798 --> 30:46.005
He thought that I lost it
'cause of my mom.

30:46.005 --> 30:49.639
Um, she was a bit of a self-medicator.

30:49.929 --> 30:52.325
I know the type.

30:57.044 --> 30:58.871
Another day, another confession.

30:58.871 --> 31:00.070
You buy it?

31:00.070 --> 31:02.472
Not the part about emailing Simon Fife.

31:02.472 --> 31:04.551
The question completely surprised him.

31:04.551 --> 31:06.845
Wouldn't be the first time
drugs addled memory.

31:06.845 --> 31:11.663
Well, except that these emails to Fife
were sent in the last three months,

31:11.663 --> 31:13.726
and Jamie's been sober that whole time.

31:13.726 --> 31:15.483
Well, if he didn't write them,
maybe his dad did.

31:15.483 --> 31:18.740
I don't see how a 12-year-old boy 
and a drunk mom

31:18.740 --> 31:20.807
could have kept a secret from Nate.

31:20.807 --> 31:22.129
Try to reach Beth.

31:22.129 --> 31:24.550
Maybe she'll meet with the kid.
He lied to us about a few things.

31:24.550 --> 31:26.619
I don't think he'll lie to her.

31:29.982 --> 31:31.664
I haven't been able to reach Beth.

31:31.664 --> 31:34.506
She might be having a bad day.
It's Halloween.

31:34.506 --> 31:35.656
Keep trying.

31:35.656 --> 31:38.284
In the meantime,
we should charge Jamie.

31:38.284 --> 31:41.265
He says he did it,
his mother covered.

31:41.265 --> 31:43.401
You don't believe a mother
would protect her 12-year-old boy?

31:43.401 --> 31:45.317
There's a piece missing.
Jamie's...

31:45.317 --> 31:46.589
maybe he's protecting his dad.

31:46.589 --> 31:49.220
It doesn't sound like
his dad protected him.

31:49.220 --> 31:53.003
Jamie has a case file in the Portland,
Oregon department of child services.

31:53.003 --> 31:56.782
He was living on the street
there when he was 16.

31:58.924 --> 32:02.458
The Royces let their son turn homeless.

32:02.458 --> 32:04.994
Well, his mom was probably
in her own world by then.

32:04.994 --> 32:07.518
Nate made a career
out of protecting Beth.

32:07.518 --> 32:09.385
Why wouldn't he get his son help?

32:09.385 --> 32:11.017
I don't know.

32:18.407 --> 32:20.768
No. He didn't want him to get help.

32:21.181 --> 32:23.274
I mean, that's, that's
the whole point, isn't it?

32:23.274 --> 32:26.415
Therapy is talk, right?

32:26.913 --> 32:30.254
A kid goes into therapy, he ends up
talking about Amberleigh's murder.

32:30.254 --> 32:32.762
When did Nate and Fife start emailing?

32:32.762 --> 32:33.571
Three months ago.

32:33.571 --> 32:37.983
Jamie told us that he was
sober for 14 weeks.

32:39.236 --> 32:41.808
You know, sobriety, that must
have been Nate's worst nightmare.

32:41.808 --> 32:44.953
'Cause when his kid is out of control,
he could control him.

32:44.953 --> 32:46.303
But if his kid's in a program...

32:46.303 --> 32:47.772
Nate was afraid his son would end up

32:47.772 --> 32:50.936
telling somebody what actually
happened that night.

32:50.936 --> 32:52.313
All right.

32:52.313 --> 32:56.146
Fife emailed Nate about
his obsession with Amberleigh.

32:56.146 --> 32:58.448
Nate reeled him in.

32:58.448 --> 33:00.739
Jamie's walking a fine line,

33:00.739 --> 33:04.224
confessing to his sins,
not his father's.

33:04.224 --> 33:06.347
Jamie won't turn on his father,

33:06.347 --> 33:09.844
but Nate, he's loyal to himself.

33:09.844 --> 33:13.632
Rich, can you find
Faith Yancy's producer?

33:13.632 --> 33:17.970
Tell them it's, uh, the DA's office.

33:19.307 --> 33:24.389
Nate Royce, your own son
has confessed to this crime.

33:24.389 --> 33:26.854
Did you ever, ever see this coming?

33:26.854 --> 33:28.622
I really shouldn't be showing you this.

33:28.622 --> 33:31.087
- Never in my wildest dreams, Faith.
- Thank you.

33:31.087 --> 33:35.025
Mr. Royce, I have some news
that may shock you.

33:35.025 --> 33:37.660
An anonymous source at the DA's office

33:37.660 --> 33:42.366
tells me that they believe your son
sent many emails to Simon Fife,

33:42.366 --> 33:44.588
pretending to be Beth Harner,

33:44.588 --> 33:48.328
giving him information
that only the killer would have.

33:48.328 --> 33:54.456
Faith, my wife Madeline
was a very sick woman,

33:54.456 --> 33:59.771
and I fear that she has
passed that on to my son.

34:02.122 --> 34:05.877
I was looking for him
in the holding cell.

34:06.964 --> 34:09.813
Detective Goren reached Beth.

34:10.039 --> 34:12.021
She's willing to meet you.

34:12.021 --> 34:13.599
Tonight.

34:14.985 --> 34:16.538
Tonight?

34:25.143 --> 34:27.206
It's all right, my baby.

34:28.514 --> 34:30.492
It's over.

34:31.619 --> 34:33.831
It's all over.

34:34.042 --> 34:36.090
Go to sleep now.

34:36.542 --> 34:38.617
I love you.

34:38.617 --> 34:41.302
Mama loves you.

34:42.341 --> 34:45.091
We all miss you, Amberleigh.

34:45.536 --> 34:47.697
Are you ready, hmm?

34:54.725 --> 34:57.497
How dare you come here, detective?

34:57.497 --> 34:59.141
Jamie wanted to pay his respects.

34:59.141 --> 35:02.382
No. No, Beth's had enough stress.

35:02.382 --> 35:04.822
No, it's all right, Nate.

35:08.814 --> 35:10.986
Come in, Jamie.

35:15.626 --> 35:17.315
Beth...

35:18.554 --> 35:20.981
I'm so sorry.

35:22.091 --> 35:24.894
You were a little boy, Jamie.

35:24.894 --> 35:26.849
I didn't mean to.

35:26.849 --> 35:28.487
It was an accident.

35:28.487 --> 35:31.590
I know. I know.

35:32.648 --> 35:34.906
Oh, you were so young.

35:34.906 --> 35:37.492
You were such a little boy.

35:41.785 --> 35:44.107
I forgive you.

35:45.682 --> 35:47.124
And so does Amberleigh.

35:47.124 --> 35:49.479
Now, come on. Come on.

36:00.472 --> 36:03.705
I wish I could take your place here.

36:08.239 --> 36:09.540
We'll drive you home, Beth.

36:09.540 --> 36:10.875
Oh, thank you.

36:10.875 --> 36:12.592
Yeah, I'd like to stay,

36:12.592 --> 36:15.467
and, and, and talk
everything over with Jamie.

36:15.467 --> 36:18.520
- No, Beth.
- It's okay, dad.

36:18.520 --> 36:20.618
I'm ready to take responsibility now.

36:20.618 --> 36:22.708
This isn't about making amends, Jamie.

36:22.708 --> 36:24.408
There are serious issues here.

36:24.408 --> 36:25.601
He already confessed, Nate.

36:25.601 --> 36:26.974
But you know that.

36:26.974 --> 36:29.787
Faith Yancy told you
all about it on national TV.

36:29.787 --> 36:32.419
Jamie and I watched.

36:32.786 --> 36:35.721
You need help, son.
That's why I went on TV,

36:35.721 --> 36:37.805
so that the public doesn't turn on you.

36:37.805 --> 36:39.637
Help. He needs help?

36:39.637 --> 36:42.020
He's getting help. He's sober.

36:42.218 --> 36:44.400
He needed help 14 years ago,

36:44.400 --> 36:45.944
the night Amberleigh died.

36:45.944 --> 36:48.728
I knew nothing about that.
My wife never told me.

36:48.728 --> 36:50.706
Even so, the drugs, the alcohol...

36:50.706 --> 36:53.173
you must have seen
your boy was in trouble.

36:53.173 --> 36:54.592
Madeline refused.

36:54.592 --> 36:59.033
I was worried about Jamie,
but she didn't care.

37:00.268 --> 37:02.087
Wait a minute, that's not true, Jamie.

37:02.087 --> 37:05.160
Your mother, your mother
cared so much about you.

37:05.160 --> 37:07.429
She was a drunk, Beth.

37:07.429 --> 37:10.570
Please. You know nothing about
my private struggles.

37:10.570 --> 37:11.756
But Jamie does.

37:11.756 --> 37:15.643
When you were in Portland, homeless,
you had a case worker.

37:15.643 --> 37:17.716
Wait a minute, you were, you were...

37:17.716 --> 37:20.304
you told me he was away at school.

37:20.304 --> 37:22.483
Your caseworker remembers you, Jamie.

37:22.483 --> 37:24.056
Do you know why?

37:24.056 --> 37:29.395
'Cause your dad called him
to request that you not get counseling.

37:29.395 --> 37:31.262
Dad, why would you?

37:31.262 --> 37:36.321
'cause he didn't want to risk you telling
your therapist your family secret.

37:36.321 --> 37:38.015
Isn't that right, Nate?

37:38.015 --> 37:40.456
When Jamie found sobriety,
you found Fife?

37:40.456 --> 37:43.778
You tricked him, didn't you,
into confessing?

37:43.778 --> 37:45.444
They're lying, Jamie.

37:45.444 --> 37:49.701
Fife had information about the murder
only the killer could've known.

37:50.262 --> 37:53.439
Fife thought that Beth was emailing him.

37:53.439 --> 37:56.033
Beth, you weren't emailing him,
were you?

37:56.266 --> 37:57.751
No.

37:57.751 --> 38:00.215
It was Jamie.
He, he doesn't remember.

38:00.215 --> 38:02.365
I didn't email him, dad.

38:02.365 --> 38:03.832
You know I love you.

38:03.832 --> 38:05.919
I have always protected you.

38:05.919 --> 38:07.586
Protected?

38:08.577 --> 38:10.708
The only one you protected
in all this was yourself.

38:10.708 --> 38:14.036
Your son could have gotten help,
but you told him he'd do hard time.

38:14.036 --> 38:15.865
Don't listen to them,
listen to me.

38:15.865 --> 38:17.574
Listen to you?

38:17.574 --> 38:19.726
You've been lying to me for 14 years.

38:19.726 --> 38:23.196
Madeline made the ransom call.

38:23.196 --> 38:26.631
Tell them, Jamie.
You came home, mom panicked.

38:26.631 --> 38:28.545
Tell them.

38:30.589 --> 38:33.154
Jamie, is that true?

38:33.340 --> 38:38.373
Jamie, Beth needs to know
what really happened.

38:42.235 --> 38:46.092
No. It wasn't mom's plan,
it was dad's.

38:46.092 --> 38:47.418
They had a big fight.

38:47.418 --> 38:51.454
I watched from the window
as mom got into the car and drove off.

38:51.454 --> 38:54.022
Dad went into the house.

38:54.796 --> 38:57.106
And I saw the light go on
in the basement,

38:57.106 --> 38:58.946
and he was down there for awhile.

38:58.946 --> 39:00.900
And then the cellar door opened,

39:00.900 --> 39:02.821
and lights went on upstairs.

39:02.821 --> 39:04.372
Did you turn the lights on, Beth?

39:04.372 --> 39:09.292
Yes, when I heard Amberleigh scream
from my bedroom window.

39:09.292 --> 39:11.134
Bedroom window, which is where?

39:11.134 --> 39:15.132
It's two floors
above the cellar door.

39:15.560 --> 39:19.328
She screamed, oh, my god,
did she scream.

39:22.266 --> 39:23.827
She was alive, Nate?

39:23.827 --> 39:25.055
No, no, no, no.

39:25.055 --> 39:27.090
She was gone, Beth.

39:27.090 --> 39:30.172
The screams were
from when Jamie was with her.

39:30.172 --> 39:32.887
So you were there.

39:32.887 --> 39:37.215
Jamie, do you remember what happened
after the lights went on?

39:37.215 --> 39:39.541
The cellar door closed,

39:39.541 --> 39:41.730
and a few minutes later,
dad came out the back door.

39:41.730 --> 39:42.939
He's got it wrong.

39:42.939 --> 39:47.855
This was his mother's idea
after Jamie killed Amberleigh.

39:47.855 --> 39:52.659
Jamie, you told me that you gave
Amberleigh a bloody nose.

39:54.201 --> 39:55.411
Did you hit her hard?

39:55.411 --> 39:58.570
No, I hit her nose by mistake,

39:58.570 --> 40:01.229
and she sat down and
started crying, and I...

40:01.229 --> 40:04.517
that's when I tried to stop the noise.

40:05.094 --> 40:07.971
And you suffocated her.

40:11.310 --> 40:13.537
But her head...

40:14.865 --> 40:17.580
her head didn't hit anything.

40:17.580 --> 40:20.186
Amberleigh's autopsy,
it's in your book. It's all there.

40:20.186 --> 40:21.916
She suffocated.

40:21.916 --> 40:27.286
And her brain had bruising,
front and back from head trauma.

40:27.286 --> 40:28.708
I didn't hit her head.

40:28.708 --> 40:30.566
All Jamie did was give her a bloody nose.

40:30.566 --> 40:32.009
He doesn't know what he did.

40:32.009 --> 40:33.908
No, but you do.

40:34.864 --> 40:36.527
Right?

40:36.527 --> 40:39.382
You saw Amberleigh in the basement.

40:39.785 --> 40:42.538
You thought she was dead,
just like Jamie did.

40:42.538 --> 40:46.891
You were gonna carry her body out,
and hide it.

40:48.755 --> 40:51.867
But something happened.

40:52.881 --> 40:54.374
What was it?

40:54.374 --> 40:56.527
Did she wake up?

40:56.744 --> 40:57.621
Did she?

40:57.621 --> 41:00.290
Nate, what did you, what did you do?

41:00.290 --> 41:02.231
She start crying?

41:02.231 --> 41:04.761
She start crying, Nate,
is that what happened?

41:04.761 --> 41:06.708
You heard Beth moving upstairs,

41:06.708 --> 41:09.133
and you panicked,
just like your son did?

41:09.133 --> 41:12.868
But Jamie ran for help from you.

41:14.361 --> 41:16.656
You smashed her head,

41:16.656 --> 41:20.353
and you threw her body into the dryer.

41:24.197 --> 41:27.457
Beth, Jamie didn't kill Amberleigh.

41:28.251 --> 41:33.810
- You did.
- I never meant...

41:34.112 --> 41:35.835
It was an accident,
and I swear that.

41:35.835 --> 41:37.552
It was an accident, huh?

41:37.552 --> 41:39.802
You sure you weren't just
trying to weigh your options?

41:39.802 --> 41:43.518
You know, her life, your reputation?

41:43.518 --> 41:45.268
And then you decided to finish her off.

41:45.268 --> 41:46.974
I was trying to protect my son.

41:46.974 --> 41:48.387
From what?

41:48.387 --> 41:51.322
You told me it was my fault,

41:51.322 --> 41:53.386
told me to act dumb.

41:53.386 --> 41:57.476
And that's what I did
for the next 14 years!

41:59.644 --> 42:02.172
How could you, Nate?

42:02.853 --> 42:04.769
How could you?

42:05.393 --> 42:06.869
Look at me.

42:08.292 --> 42:10.175
Nate, look at me.

42:10.354 --> 42:11.247
Look at me.

42:11.247 --> 42:12.777
All right, get him out of here.

42:12.777 --> 42:14.629
Look at me!

42:18.598 --> 42:21.306
You took everything.

